        public java.lang.Object internalValue()
        Description copied from class: ObjectId
        Must be implemented to return the internal value of this instance. This method exists mainly to provide access to the internal ID representation for frameworks. Implementations should only return immutable objects. For primitive types an instance the corresponding wrapper class must be returned.
